Description: It is unknown by whom or for what purpose this wooden idol carved in the likeness of the auspice Byakko was created.
Name: Byakko Totem

Description:
A uniquely crafted lens discovered in the Sigmascape.

Two lenses can be traded for special headgear.
Name: Sigmascape Lens

Description:
A uniquely crafted shaft discovered in the Sigmascape.

Four shafts can be traded for special body gear.
Name: Sigmascape Shaft

Description:
A uniquely crafted crank discovered in the Sigmascape.

Two cranks can be traded for special arm gear.
Name: Sigmascape Crank

Description:
A uniquely crafted spring discovered in the Sigmascape.

Four springs can be traded for special leg gear.
Name: Sigmascape Spring

Description:
A uniquely crafted pedal discovered in the Sigmascape.

Two pedals can be traded for special foot gear.
Name: Sigmascape Pedal

Description: A uniquely crafted chain discovered in the Sigmascape. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered it worthless.
Name: Sigmascape Chain

Description:
A uniquely crafted bolt discovered in the Sigmascape.

One bolt can be traded for a special accessory.
Name: Sigmascape Bolt

Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged in the Sigmascape.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.
Name: Sigmascape Datalog v1.0

Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged in the Sigmascape.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.
Name: Sigmascape Datalog v2.0

Detailed records of past battles waged in the Sigmascape.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.
Name: Sigmascape Datalog v3.0

Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged in the Sigmascape.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.
Name: Sigmascape Datalog v4.0

Description: A remarkable crystalline fragment within which can be seen images from another world. Though such articles were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up, leaving them with little value as bartering materials.
Name: Sigmascape Crystalloid

Description: A dissolving agent concocted by Doman artisans that, when applied to certain weapons, heightens their attributes by removing impurities on their surface. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Ryumyaku Solvent

Description: A durable thread used by Doman artisans. When woven into certain armor, it is believed to heighten its attributes. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Ryumyaku Twine

Description: A slightly corrosive paste concocted by Doman goldsmiths that, when applied to certain accessories, heightens their attributes by restoring their luster. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Ryumyaku Polish

Description: A note of promise received from Rowena for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of mendacity or poetics. However, due to the House of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.
Name: Rowena's Token (Mendacity)

Description: Garlond Ironworks engineers believe this device to be an attempt by Allagan scientists to increase tomestone capacity, while keeping overall size relatively small. This may have become the next standard in tomestone data storage...had not their civilization been inconveniently wiped from the realm. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.
Name: Prototype Tomestone

Description:
A heavy chest containing a diamond weapon.

Required level: 70. IL: 375. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.
Name: Diamond Weapon Coffer (IL 375)

Description: Comprising the front end of a shark-class submersible, this bow has been reinforced to double as a battering ram for subduing unruly sea creatures.
Name: Shark-class Bow

Description: Comprising the top of a shark-class submersible, the bridge houses all of the equipment necessary for the vessel's crew to navigate the unplumbed depths of the Ruby Sea and beyond.
Name: Shark-class Bridge

Description: Comprising the center of a shark-class submersible, this ovoid hull is multi-walled to stabilize and maintain pressure within so that the vessel's crew does not succumb to the crushing weight of the waters it navigates. Several sturdy rudder fins serve to increase maneuverability.
Name: Shark-class Pressure Hull

Description: Comprising the rear end of a shark-class submersible, this stern contains the unique independent engine which propels the craft.
Name: Shark-class Stern

Description: Unlike the bows of most submersibles, the unkiu-class model is outfitted with rudder fins usually relegated to the stern.
Name: Unkiu-class Bow

Description: Designed by the Onishishu─a collective of skilled Far Eastern craftsmen─this submersible bridge differs dramatically in build from those built in the West.
Name: Unkiu-class Bridge

Description: Comprising the center of an unkiu-class submersible, this ovoid hull is multi-walled to stabilize and maintain pressure within so that the vessel's crew does not succumb to the crushing weight of the waters it navigates. Supplemental propulsion engines have been affixed to the sides to increase underwater speed.
Name: Unkiu-class Pressure Hull

Description: Comprising the rear end of an unkiu-class submersible, this stern contains a double propeller engine.
Name: Unkiu-class Stern

Description:
This crystalline prism captures the likeness of a piece of equipment and projects it onto another object of comparable form and function.

[Necessary to project glamours.]
Name: Glamour Prism

Description: The elemental energies of this unstable crystal are in a perpetual state of flux.
Name: Protean Crystal

Description: A foul feather plucked from the Eurekan nightmare, Pazuzu.
Name: Pazuzu's Feather

Description: A crystal discovered in Eureka Anemos─a region where the elemental aspect leans heavily to wind.
Name: Anemos Crystal

Description: Common in the Far East, futons are thin down-filled mattresses laid directly on the floor instead of upon a frame. After use, they are generally rolled up and stored in a closet until needed again.
Name: Futon Mattress

Description: An expertly woven tapestry displayed during Hatching-tide festivities.
Name: Hatching-tide Banner

Description: An indoor lantern designed to resemble the oddest of otters.
Name: Odder Otter Lantern

Description: A Heavensturn decoration displayed at homes and places of business. The spinning umbrella is thought to bring fortune as long as an object remains atop.
Name: Boar's Head Kadomatsu

Description: When faced with the dilemma of adorning his wall with a normal chronometer or a chronometer carved in the adorable likeness of a moogle, it is said the dread (though most likely nonexistent) pirate Mustbeard replied with a hearty “arrr” and found room for both.
Name: Moogle Wall Chronometer

Description:
A round desk carved to resemble Byakko, one of the mystic Four Lords of the Far East.

※One per estate only.
Name: Byakko Sideboard

Description:
A regal throne, fit for a king...or emperor that also happens to be a giant white tiger.

※One per estate only.
Name: Byakko Throne

Description: So realistic is this stuffed spriggan that many a mage has lost face after sending one up in a gout of sorcerous flame.
Name: Stuffed Spriggan

Description: A trophy awarded to those who “left their mark” in Season Six of the Feast.
Name: Season Six Lone Wolf Trophy

Description: Without proper advertisement, some may mistake Valentione's Day for any other day, albeit one with far more pink balloons.
Name: Valentione's Day Advertisement

Description: To create these festive balloons, the bladders of various flying fish caught in the Sea of Clouds were dried, colored, then stamped with the House Valentione coat of arms before being filled with heated air to keep them afloat.
Name: Valentione's Day Balloons

Description: Aromatic loaves of freshly baked bread fill this wicker basket to the brim. ※Cannot be retrieved once used. ※Can be used up to 10 times. Meal benefits when used: Tenacity Bonus: +4% (Max 12) VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8) Gear Durability Bonus: +2 EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Bread Basket

Description: A charming recreation of the chocobo Alpha, filled with the feathers of a fowl less fortunate.
Name: Stuffed Alpha

Description: A faithful replication of the selfsame set used every morning by Aymeric de Borel himself. ※Cannot be retrieved once used. ※Can be used up to 10 times. Meal benefits when used: Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 12) VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8) Gear Durability Bonus: +2 EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: House Borel Tea Set

Description: The design used on this quaint porcelain tea set is based off a passage in an ancient literary work on Halicarnassus, Queen of Dimension Castle. ※Cannot be retrieved once used. ※Can be used up to 10 times. Meal benefits when used: Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 12) VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8) Gear Durability Bonus: +2 EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)
Name: Royal Dowager Tea Set

Description: An interior wall built with genuine kiln-fired bricks.
Name: Brick Interior Wall

Description: A space-saving cupboard that can be mounted anywhere there is a wall.
Name: Mounted Cupboard

Description: The vegetables contained within this basket have not been approved for consumption. Dine at your own risk.
Name: Vegetable Basket

Description: A low partition cut with a hole to provide estates with the illusion of more space than actually exists.
Name: Open Partition

Description: An island for kitchens designed to resemble those carts used by hawkers in city markets.
Name: Counter Cart

Description: A decorative cabinet designed in the Old World Sharlayan style.
Name: Sharlayan Cabinet

Description: A decorative wardrobe designed in the Old World Sharlayan style.
Name: Sharlayan Wardrobe

Description: A small tub crafted to resemble a summoner's best friend. Just large enough for two.
Name: Carbuncle Bathtub

Description: From scalpels to saws, panaceas to placebos, this basic set of medical devices has everything the unlicensed surgeon needs.
Name: Chirurgeon's Essentials

Description: Save space in your cupboards for liquor and fruitcake by hanging all your kitchen appliances from hooks.
Name: Kitchen Hanger

Description: A frightening mask of Far Eastern design. Perfect for children's bedrooms and nurseries.
Name: Hanya Mask

Description: A set of Hingan bottles and cups perfect for taking one's evening refreshment with guests─though using it to take one's afternoon refreshment alone is not unheard of.
Name: Sake Set

Description: A large white panel used by acting troupes as a simple backdrop for plays.
Name: Stage Panel

Description: Those without a deathly fear of snakes claim this plush doll to be one of the most beautiful ever crafted. Most ophidiophobes, however, would beg to differ.
Name: Stuffed Ananta

Description:
A small, reinforced glass tank that, when filled with water, can serve as a home for select wavekin caught in the wild. The higher an aquarium's tier, the larger the specimens that can be kept within.
※Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 aquariums, respectively.
Name: Tier 1 Metal Aquarium

Description:
A reinforced glass tank that, when filled with water, can serve as a home for select wavekin caught in the wild. The higher an aquarium's tier, the larger the specimens that can be kept within.
※Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 aquariums, respectively.
Name: Tier 2 Metal Aquarium

Description: Not one to be humbled by craftsmen of the East, a prominent Eorzean lamp maker conceived this fixture he hopes will become the new standard in home and garden lighting.
Name: Eorzean Lantern

Description: A cast-iron wood stove designed after a fateful encounter with a voidsent bomb.
Name: Bomb Stove

Description: A decorative pillar designed in the Hingan fashion.
Name: Hingan Pillar

Description: What better way to tell unwanted visitors, “can't you see I'm busy?” than by strewing stacks of important-looking documents all about your humble abode?
Name: Stack of Documents

Description: Countless varieties of rouges, putties, and talcums commonly used by mummers to prepare themselves for their acts.
Name: Mummer's Maquillage

Description: Because one wouldn't dare hang a dress on a coat hanger.
Name: Dress Hanger

Description: An oversized locker used by mummers to house not only their costumes, but their various tools of the trade.
Name: Mummer's Wardrobe

Description: A tiered dais used in the Far East to display dolls. Adapted in Eorzea for use on Little Ladies' Day.
Name: Far Eastern Doll Display

Description: Because one wouldn't dare hang a coat on a dress hanger.
Name: Coat Hanger

Description: Make profane offerings from the comfort of your home with this sinister altar to the high voidsent Pazuzu.
Name: Altar to Pazuzu

Description: A pushcart filled with thousands upon thousands of fragrant roses (give or take a few thousand).
Name: Rose Wagon

Description: A low-growing hedge, expertly pruned and trimmed into the shape of an L.
Name: Corner Hedge Partition

Description: A controlled cluster of bamboo cut from a Yanxian forest for display in private gardens.
Name: Bamboo Copse

Description: Scalding water tapped from the very bowels of the land, and collected in a quaint rock pool certain to draw the envy of neighbors.
Name: Hingan Hot Spring

Description: A wall that matches the design of those used in Aymeric de Borel's very manor.
Name: House Borel Interior Wall

Description: Smooth, elegant floor tiling made of polished marble.
Name: White Marble Flooring

Description: A lavish light fixture that hearkens to days long past.
Name: Classic Chandelier

Description:
A fully functional moogle-themed orchestrion for the moogle-lover who has everything...but a fully functional moogle-themed orchestrion.

※One orchestrion of any type per estate only.
Name: Melodious Mogchestrion

Description:
An authentic reproduction of the perfect way to say “I love you” without having your hands torn to shreds by thousands of prickly rose thorns.

Select flowers can be displayed within.
Name: Authentic Paramour Vase

Description: An authentic reproduction of one of hundreds of hand-drawn images posted about Ul'dah in preparation for Little Ladies' Day.
Name: Authentic Little Ladies' Day Advertisement

Description: There is nothing quite as ephemeral as a single pink cherry petal dancing in the wind as it makes its long descent from tree to earth, just as there is nothing quite as exhilarating as jumping in an authentic reproduction of a drift of tens of thousands of said petals.
Name: Authentic Eastern Cherry Petal Pile

Description: An authentic reproduction of an interior wall designed to complement private Hatching–tide celebrations.
Name: Authentic Eggstravagant Interior Wall

Description:
Several hard, brown bulbs the size of a gigantoad's eye.

※For use in planters.
